reviews.review: Booooorrrrriiinnnggg my friend fell asleep and I was so bored whereas I can usually sit through most boring movies but this one was just uninteresting and bland I’ve watched all of the Star Wars movies as well
Was a fun and at times emotional ride to an end of a saga.

The Rise of Skywalker brings what we wanted from the force awakens. Rey, Ben, palpatine everything. The final few minutes of the movie brought me to tears knowing that the story has come full cycle. With all the Jedi from the previous films playing their part and the conclusion to the saga, I thoroughly enjoyed it.

The Rise of Skywalker was hands-down the best of the new trilogy. It packs a lot in. This story should have been two movies: Episodes 8 and 9.

Rey finally became a viable and interesting character just in time for the trilogy to end. I'd like to see more movies about her, now. Before this installment, I didn't care what happened to her.

It's a big big big movie!
It was nice that they brought back everyone.  It wrapped up things okay.  It had obvious plot flaws, and the plot was obvious.  It was better than the last two in the series, but still overhyped.

Terrible.If you want to watch a random action movie its okay,but if you have ever seen a star wars movie before,your brain will hurt after watching this one.Its so bad it even messes with the previous installments in the saga.
Liked the story , especially how the past spirit came to  leave important messages
Not as great as all the hype

I’t comes off a little forces at times and need some character arch storyline completed and not just briefly explained. Some decent light saber work but nothing great. It missed some good opportunities for jaw dropping moments.

Its a good way to end the saga but tbh for the next future movies for Star Wars, atleast let the Jedi (REY) use more of the lightsaber when shes getting shot or in a battle with stormtroopers or etc. They could of atleast see when anakin and obi wan got out of there flight and started blocking the shots from the droids.
